Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.54,0:02:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The day after the ground wept, the sun rose an hour earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.75,0:02:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It set only 15 minutes early,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.86,0:02:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and no one noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.46,0:02:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, someone noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.62,0:02:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was a mere note scribbled down on parchment, lost and forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.11,0:02:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Until two weeks later, when the sun rose \Nan hour late and set two hours early.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.77,0:02:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Darkness was creeping in slowly, like hounds after a scent.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.26,0:02:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Ender man smelling blood in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.31,0:02:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,By late Reapmoon, there were only five and a\Nhalf hours of daylight, instead of the usual 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.61,0:02:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the thirstiest noticed the lack of light,\Nalong with the lack of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.25,0:02:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Then came no sun at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.01,0:02:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The darkness was impenetrable, even for the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.77,0:02:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh how they hoped and prayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.11,0:03:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The winter solstice would see dawn come again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.07,0:03:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, she denied them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.90,0:03:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The month of Dawnbloom came and went, and for the first time\Nin memory,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.52,0:03:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,without Dawn ever blooming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.00,0:03:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hope began to decay, and desperation began forming like a\Nmould.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.80,0:03:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All of Vaildin would soon be rotting from within.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.29,0:03:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If not Dawnbloom, then perhaps during the Stormbloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.10,0:03:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"Perhaps the storms will bring us the sun?" they begged.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.93,0:03:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But the storms did not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.03,0:03:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,"Rasroth the Water Stealer"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.86,0:03:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"Rasroth the Salt Bringer"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.19,0:03:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,"Rasroth the Sun Eater" is driven out of God's Din Keep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.66,0:04:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But, out of respect for his brother the king, and the\Nsacrifice of his two wards as penance,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.95,0:04:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He is not killed then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.39,0:04:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That night is the last night of Stormbloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.58,0:04:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, for the first time in four months, dawn splinters like\Na revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.14,0:04:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But she stays only an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.84,0:04:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire month of green bloom, when spring should be\Nrenewing Din,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.20,0:04:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the frosts melting and plants growing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.15,0:04:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Trees budding.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.40,0:04:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing growing, is unrest against the Crown.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.56,0:04:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing budding, plots.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.73,0:04:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The fastest growing {\i1}anything{\i0} are the whispers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.61,0:04:49.04,Top,,0,0,0,,(Help me when we cast him out.)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.33,0:04:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was only once the heir presumptive\Nwas cast out that the sun returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.14,0:04:55.12,Top,,0,0,0,,(Perhaps more is needed?)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.62,0:04:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The only new growth this Greenbloom is treason.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.54,0:05:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.05,0:05:02.08,Top,,0,0,0,,(That's treason! No, it's a revolution...)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.41,0:05:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The day of the Rosebloom equinox,\Nthe Sun rises at six, and sets at six.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.96,0:05:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,After 12 hours of daylight, night falls, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.74,0:05:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so does the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.45,0:05:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The first rose bloom, of Rosebloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.21,0:05:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The King, of course, does not rise again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.55,0:05:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Dawn, however, rises every single day after that,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.65,0:05:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,as if breaking a fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.71,0:05:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Two weeks from now, after the sun has\Nset for the last time on the King,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.59,0:05:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the sun will not set at all.
